{"id":"1605.07839","submitter":"Ikkei Hotta","authors":"Ikkei Hotta","title":"Loewner chains with quasiconformal extensions: an approximation approach","comments":"18 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CV","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A new approach in Loewner Theory proposed by Bracci, Contreras,\nD\\'iaz-Madrigal and Gumenyuk provides a unified treatment of the radial and the\nchordal versions of the Loewner equations. In this framework, a generalized\nLoewner chain satisfies the differential equation $$ \\partial_{t}f_{t}(z) = (z\n- \\tau(t))(1-\\overline{\\tau(t)}z)\\partial_{z}f_{t}(z)p(z,t), $$ where $\\tau :\n[0,\\infty) \\to \\overline{\\mathbb{D}}$ is measurable and $p$ is called a\nHerglotz function. In this paper, we will show that if there exists a $k \\in\n[0,1)$ such that $p$ satisfies $$ |p(z,t) - 1| \\leq k |p(z,t) + 1| $$ for all\n$z \\in \\mathbb{D}$ and almost all $t \\in [0,\\infty)$, then $f_{t}$ has a\n$k$-quasiconformal extension to the whole Riemann sphere for all $t \\in\n[0,\\infty)$. The radial case ($\\tau =0$) and the chordal case ($\\tau=1$) have\nbeen proven by Becker [J. Reine Angew. Math. \\textbf{255} (1972), 23-43] and\nGumenyuk and the author (Math. Z. \\textbf{285} (2017), no.3, 1063--1089). In\nour theorem, no superfluous assumption is imposed on $\\tau \\in\n\\overline{\\mathbb{D}}$. As a key foundation of our proof is an approximation\nmethod using the continuous dependence of evolution families.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 May 2016 11:53:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Aug 2016 06:29:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 7 May 2017 08:15:37 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 15 Feb 2019 19:54:14 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 1 Mar 2019 17:49:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-04"}
