ervariables - (i)\nunusually luminous tidal disruption events; (ii) extinction events; (iii)\nchanges in accretion state; and (iv) large amplitude microlensing by stars in\nforeground galaxies. A mixture of explanations (iii) and (iv) seems most\nlikely. Both hold promise of considerable new insight into the AGN phenomenon.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 May 2016 11:59:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Aug 2016 13:41:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-21"}
